  1→/**
  2→ * Integration tests for the remote access auth pipeline.
  3→ *
  4→ * These tests exercise the FULL middleware chain + routes + services
  5→ * with a real in-memory SQLite database. Nothing is mocked except:
  6→ *   - getDatabase() (returns our test-local in-memory DB)
  7→ *   - getServerPort() (health.ts imports server.ts which has side effects)
  8→ *
  9→ * What this proves that unit tests can't:
 10→ *   - Middleware ordering: remote-gate -> CORS -> auth -> route handlers
 11→ *   - Real SHA-256 hashing: createDeviceToken() stores hash, validateDeviceToken() finds it
 12→ *   - Real Zod validation: PairBody schema rejects malformed requests
 13→ *   - Settings cache invalidation: toggling remote_access_enabled actually gates access
 14→ *   - One-time pairing codes: generate -> use -> refuse reuse
 15→ */
